'''''Zoyon Patrol''''' is an educational [[simulation game]] for the [[Apple II]] published by [[Minnesota Educational Computing Consortium|MECC]] in 1987. The player is the director of the Zoyon patrol, located on the fictional Zaphyr Island (supposedly located at 7°52' S, and 178º28' E, which is approximately 7 miles NE of [[Nukufetau|Nukufetau, Tuvalu]], in the south Pacific).

Zoyons are fictional creatures, whose names and features are combination of pre-existing creatures.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zoyon Patrol for Apple II (1987) |url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/zoyon-patrol |access-date=2022-04-27 |website=MobyGames}}</ref> For instance one Zoyon is called Catamonk, and it shares feature of a Cat and Monkey. An Elecoon has features of an Elephant and a Racoon.

==Gameplay==
As the director of the Zoyon Patrol, the player is charged with taking messages about Zoyons, identifying the Zoyon in question, trapping it alive, and arranging for its safe return to its native habitat.  Every Zoyon is to be considered an endangered species.

